Then, combine one 'artificial, soft, cut' item with one 'natural, hard, finely cut' item. This combination yields an item with 80 value. Finally, use the 'frame' tool on this combined item to reach the maximum value of 100. Note: Scissors can be used on multiple items until all are cut; the frame tool is used once on the combined item.

message: To score 100: Cut soft items once and hard items twice. Always cut before combining, and prioritize cutting soft items first. message: To win, always 'cut' all soft items once first. They become 'cut' and gain value. For hard items, 'cut' them twice; the first cut might be negative, but the second cut ('finely cut') often makes them valuable. There are two main paths to 100 points: 1. Combine a 'cut artificial, soft' item with a 'cut natural, soft' item, then 'frame' the result. This is the most consistent path. 2. message: To reach 100 points, always cut all ingredients before combining. For soft items, cut them once with scissors (value +25). For hard items, cut them twice with scissors; the first cut will be negative (-30), but the second cut will make it 'finely cut' (+25), which is essential. Always process soft items with scissors first. There are two main successful combinations: 1) combine a 'cut' artificial soft item with a 'finely cut' natural hard item, then apply the 'frame' tool. 2) combine a 'cut' artificial soft item with a 'cut' natural soft item, then apply the 'frame' tool. Both combinations, once framed, yield 100 points.
